---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
const updated = "June 15, 2026";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Clad"
  description="How CladFacts (cladfacts.com) handles your information: no accounts, no tracking, no advertising."
>
  <article class="static-page">
    <h2 class="static-page__title">Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="dateline">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how CladFacts ("Clad," "we," "us") handles
      information in connection with the website at
      <strong>cladfacts.com</strong> (the "Site"). Clad is an independent
      political fact-checking publication. The Site is read-only for visitors:
      there are no user accounts, logins, comments, newsletters, or purchases.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">The short version</h3>
    <p>
      We don't want your data and we don't try to collect it. The Site has
      <strong>no advertising, no analytics, no third-party trackers, and no user
      accounts.</strong> We don't sell or share personal information, because we
      don't gather it.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Information we collect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>No personal information from visitors.</strong> You can read the
        Site without giving us any personal details. We don't ask for, or store,
        names, emails, or accounts for readers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Standard server logs.</strong> The Site is hosted on Cloudflare,
        which—like any web host—processes basic technical request data (such as
        IP address, browser type, and pages requested) to deliver the Site,
        defend against abuse, and keep it online. This is handled by Cloudflare
        under its own terms; we do not use it to build profiles of readers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>If you email us.</strong> If you contact the editor at
        <a href="mailto:editor@cladfacts.com">editor@cladfacts.com</a>, we
        receive whatever you put in that message and use it only to respond.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Cookies</h3>
    <p>
      The Site sets <strong>no advertising or analytics cookies</strong> and uses
      no cross-site trackers. It may set a strictly necessary cookie for basic
      security and functionality. Note that pages embedding a YouTube player load
      content from YouTube, which may set its own cookies and collect data when
      you interact with a video—see the section below.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Third-party content and links</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Embedded YouTube videos.</strong> Reports may embed the original
        source video from YouTube. When you play an embedded video, Google/YouTube
        may collect data and set cookies under
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Hosting.</strong> The Site runs on Cloudflare, subject to
        Cloudflare's privacy practices.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Outbound links.</strong> Reports link to original sources and
        cited material on other websites. We are not responsible for the privacy
        practices of sites we link to.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Children</h3>
    <p>
      The Site is intended for a general audience and is not directed to children
      under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from them.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Your choices</h3>
    <p>
      Because we don't collect personal information from readers, there's little
      to access, correct, or delete. If you've emailed us and want that
      correspondence removed, ask and we will delete it.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Changes</h3>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the Site evolves. Material changes will be
      reflected by the "Last updated" date above.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub" id="contact">Contact</h3>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy? Email
      <a href="mailto:editor@cladfacts.com">editor@cladfacts.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="static-page__note">
      This page describes the website only. It is provided for transparency and
      is not legal advice.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
